^-{ ^*BDeal of the Week #191 - May 8, 2000^*N }
^-
This week's deal was played by ^*BVicent Ramondt^*N of The Netherlands during the recent ^*BPolitiken World Pairs^*N in Copenhagen, Denmark. Ramondt and partner, ^*BAnton Maas^*N, finished a strong 5th of the 16 pairs who were invited to play in the 2000 Politiken. Ramondt and Mass faced the eventual winners, Italians ^*BNorberto Bocchi^*N and ^*BGiorgio Dubion^*N, when this week's deal was played. The deal has been rotated to make South the declarer. We would like to thank ^*BEric Kokish^*N for telling us about this week's deal.

Before we get started, here is the answer to the problem that was posed last week:

You are declarer in 5@C and have no losers outside the trump suit. Your trumps are:

|cs|3|at|^-{ @C^*B AQ108765^*N }
^-
Unfortunately the dummy is void in trump. After winning the opening lead you lay down the @CA and both defenders follow small. How do you continue?

